id: pm-oxrw
title: "Promote governance, validation, health, and maintenance primitives to the public SDK: validate, health, gc, changelog/reporting hooks"
description: "Typed SDK access to the governance engine (metadata profiles, resolution checks, lifecycle rules, file-link validation, history-drift), health checks, and gc/maintenance so integrators can enforce the same quality bars programmatically. Duplicate check: no existing governance-primitive SDK item."
type: Feature
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags[3]: architecture,"area:governance","area:sdk"
created_at: "2026-07-05T04:54:11.132Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-15T10:10:01.145Z"
assignee: codex-root
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 360
acceptance_criteria: SDK exports typed validate/health/gc primitives returning the same structured check results the CLI prints; ops commands consume only these primitives; docstrings + linked tests + SDK reference docs; zero behavior change
parent: pm-usfg
risk: low
confidence: medium
resolution: "Moved validation, health, and garbage-collection implementations into public SDK governance modules with CLI compatibility adapters."
expected_result: Packages and embedded applications can invoke the same typed governance primitives as the CLI without importing presentation code.
actual_result: "Public SDK exports runValidate, runHealth, and runGc from SDK-owned modules; CLI and runtime consume those modules and all gates pass."
