comments[14]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-06T21:58:32.680Z",maintainer-agent,"Audit #15 scope note: decide telemetry-queue/runtime primitives here — either promote them with validate/health/gc (they share the ops noun per pm-6apl) or explicitly document them as CLI-only in the SDK reference. The SDK domain matrix should leave no command family unmapped."
  "2026-07-07T20:44:48.118Z",codex-agent,"Implementation start: bundled governance/health/maintenance SDK primitives with adjacent SDK-context work. Live duplicate/context check found this domain still open; telemetry queue/runtime decision will be documented in SDK docs rather than hidden."
  "2026-07-08T06:06:37.127Z",codex,"Evidence: broad command/runtime coverage remained green after the SDK public-result hardening: node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 266 files / 5459 tests with 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines."
  "2026-07-15T06:48:49.673Z",codex-root,"Implementation scope 2026-07-15: extract typed validate/health/gc/remediation primitives into the public SDK, make CLI adapters consume them, preserve output contracts, and pair the promotion with cross-platform nightly and release-gate proof. This is the primary feature item for the wide bundle."
  "2026-07-15T07:25:17.739Z",codex-root,"Evidence: validate, health, and gc implementations now live under src/sdk/governance and are exported directly by the public SDK; CLI modules are thin compatibility adapters. Runtime no longer sources these primitives from CLI code. Full 5,721-test coverage is 100/100/100/100; static quality, 100% docstrings, package boundary, context evaluation, docs, secrets, 88-command dogfood, and packed-npx acceptance all pass."
  "2026-07-15T07:34:37.998Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile review 0b7745fd-4cf0-43db-a31d-f89048a4d524 confidence 4/5: accepted all three P2 observations. Attribution baseline epoch is precomputed once; Windows embedded quotes now use native cmd doubled-quote escaping with regression coverage. Focused tests and strict static gates pass."
  "2026-07-15T07:56:48.602Z",codex-root,"Hosted correction evidence: path-keyed legacy lint suppressions now follow the promoted SDK health/validate modules, and author provenance classification is a documented reusable SDK primitive under the strict complexity ceiling. Focused 61-test regression, ESLint, static quality/docstrings/package boundary/token gates, and the complete 291-file/5,721-test suite pass with exact 100% statements (37,004/37,004), branches (26,554/26,554), functions (7,458/7,458), and lines (36,119/36,119)."
  "2026-07-15T08:12:17.071Z",codex-root,"PR #568 correction pushed at e8f13696 after exact-head local Greptile review 54a59c37-3f4c-43ba-a2b1-0764160e2077 returned 5/5 with no comments. Hosted Greptile, Gemini, and CodeRabbit were retriggered because the PR head changed."
  "2026-07-15T08:29:31.384Z",codex-root,"DeepSource correction evidence: accepted all three inline findings on the author-attribution SDK primitive. The exported classifier is now an arrow constant (module-scope hygiene), and classifier/stream branching was reduced below medium-risk cyclomatic thresholds with typed counters while preserving malformed JSON handling and original JSONL line numbers. Focused 147-test governance regression, strict static gates, and the full 291-file/5,721-test suite pass at exact 100/100/100/100 coverage."
  "2026-07-15T08:47:10.844Z",codex-root,"DeepSource second-pass evidence: rerun reduced classifier complexity from 9 to 6 and exposed the neighboring stream declaration. Final correction removes the remaining classifier decision through nullish normalization and expresses classifier, stream inspector, and async scanner uniformly as exported arrow constants. Focused 147 tests, strict static gates, and full 5,721-test exact 100/100/100/100 coverage pass."
  "2026-07-15T09:27:56.232Z",codex-root,"Review adjudication 2026-07-15: accepted actionable author warnings as blocking overall health, complete CommandLineToArgvW quote/backslash escaping, and junction-compatible Windows copy tests. Rejected the relative-destination crash report because copyExtensionDirectoryWithoutSelfNesting resolves the destination with path.resolve before parsing its root. Defensive legacy-payload guards do not apply to private helpers fed directly by the same-process typed scanner; full-stream performance suggestions describe pre-existing opt-in integrity/compaction behavior and remain under the scale roadmap rather than changing this compatibility move. Focused 195 tests, typecheck, formatting, and strict quality gates pass."
  "2026-07-15T09:39:03.792Z",codex-root,"Greptile pre-push review evidence (2026-07-15): accepted P1 finding comment-1784108230323-vfmohmi. Missing or invalid timestamps now classify unknown-author history as legacy informational data; only parseable post-baseline events are actionable. Added explicit missing/invalid timestamp regression coverage. Focused author-attribution and health suites pass (59 tests), typecheck passes, and diff check is clean."
  "2026-07-15T09:59:24.789Z",codex-root,"Pre-push exhaustive proof (2026-07-15): exact-head Greptile confirmation returned confidence 5/5 with zero comments. Full coverage passed 291 files / 5,721 tests at statements 37,014/37,014, branches 26,532/26,532, functions 7,463/7,463, lines 36,129/36,129. Aggregate release gates passed build, typecheck, docs/skills, strict static quality and 100% docstrings, package boundary, token budgets, version sync, secrets scan, packed npx smoke, and the isolated 88-command package-first dogfood. Live telemetry is healthy at 0.33% finish error rate with zero missing error codes; only Sentry PM-CLI-2B/29 remain, owned by pm-d4ns/pm-7n5a and their owner-repository PRs."
  "2026-07-15T10:10:01.145Z",codex-root,"Hosted analyzer correction (2026-07-15): accepted GitHub code-scanning alert 26 (CodeQL polynomial-regex risk) and the renewed DeepSource classifier-complexity finding on PR #568 head 092de7ae. Windows CommandLineToArgvW rendering now uses a linear character scanner with explicit pending-backslash accounting; author attribution uses a typed unknown-author/post-baseline policy matrix, keeping missing or invalid timestamps legacy without control-flow complexity. Focused 66 tests, typecheck, strict static/docstring/package/token gates, and full 291-file/5,721-test coverage pass at exact 100/100/100/100 (37,023 statements, 26,530 branches, 7,463 functions, 36,138 lines)."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T17:45:58.049Z",maintainer-agent,"Promotion slicing S1-S4 (pass #53 code survey). Territory = ~5.1k lines of CLI-side domain logic: validate.ts 2623 + health.ts 2161 + gc.ts 341; SDK index exports NOTHING for validate/health/gc today. Both blockers (pm-lodl, pm-muhw) closed - actionable now.\nS1 validate check-engine (~150m): check orchestration lives in cli/commands/validate.ts - it imports core scanners (scanHistoryDrift, findDuplicateIssueCodes, buildMissingByTypeCounts, core/validate/* helpers) but assembles checks/counts/worklists inside the command. Extract a typed check-producer registry into core/validate/ and export runValidateChecks() returning the same structured envelope (checks[].status, *_count scalars, details.*_item_ids); validate.ts shrinks to flag-parse + render.\nS2 health probe registry (~120m): same move for health.ts - probes (store layout, scanLockHealth, vectorization staleness via collectStaleVectorizationIds, extension registrations, history drift + stream policy) become typed producers; export runHealthProbes(). Natural fix site for GH-457/pm-tu71 - promotion adds a per-probe timeout surface.\nS3 gc primitive (~45m): gc.ts is small (341 lines, 4 fns); export typed gc plan/apply primitive; CLI consumes it.\nS4 reporting/remediation hooks (~60m): expose buildRemediationCommands (core/diagnostics/remediation.ts) through the SDK; type the changelog/reporting hooks; docstrings + linked tests + SDK reference docs for S1-S3 exports.\nZero-behavior-change gate: validate/health/gc CLI JSON output byte-identical, existing specs green. Recommended entry: S1 (largest file, self-contained)."
